      <div class="msgContentFrame">So I'm curious if anyone else has been doing this.  I recently got my LNC to 20 and got the skill Feint.  I mainly leveled GLA for Still Percision, but I found that using a dagger and spamming phalanax/feint is an amazing combo for soloing.  I had no acc + rings and still was doing around 100-150 per attack even if I miss.  And with daggers being Piercing/Slashing, the Feint damage was alot higher than on a class like MAR. <br /> <br />But now since GLA is getting closer to 20, does anyone know if Feint does decent threat, or does it just seem like a normal melee attack with bonus damage. <br /> <br />(On a side note, on my LNC I tend to take aggro here and there from feint spamming, but that might just be because with feint I never &quot;miss&quot; an attack.</div>
